SIMPLE: arachnida
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Arachnida
<hw>A*rach"ni*da</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ spider.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the classes of
Arthropoda. See <xex>Illustration</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ They have four pairs of legs, no antenn⟦ae⟧ nor wings, a
pair of mandibles, and one pair of maxill⟦ae⟧ or palpi. The head is
usually consolidated with the thorax. The respiration is either by
tranche⟦ae⟧ or by pulmonary sacs, or by both. The class includes three
principal orders: <stype><spn>Araneina</spn></stype>, or spiders;
<stype><spn>Arthrogastra</spn></stype>, including scorpions, etc.; and
<stype><spn>Acarina</spn></stype>, or mites and ticks.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arachnidan</ent>⟦br⟧
